      .collect();

distinct_values is O(n²) (linear-scan iter().any(grouped_scalar_eq)) —
left intentionally that way to support the cross-dtype caller
DataFrame::nunique_axis1 (which pulls row-wise values from columns of
potentially different dtypes).

But this caller is iterating COLUMNS (axis=0) — each column is
homogeneous in dtype (Column::new validation), so ScalarKey-based
dedup is safe and O(n). Series::nunique_with_dropna already uses that
path (br-15f51).

